# Build context for the BACKEND image (deployments/Dockerfile, context = repo root).
# The Go build needs only go.mod/go.sum + the Go source tree + configs/. Everything
# else is excluded — for speed, image size, and to NEVER leak secrets into the image.
# (The web frontend builds from its own context web/ with web/.dockerignore.)

.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.worktrees/

# The web app is NOT embedded in the Go binary — exclude it entirely (1GB+ of
# node_modules / .next would otherwise be sent as build context).
web/

# Dependencies / build outputs anywhere.
**/node_modules
dist/
bin/
*.exe

# Secrets & runtime state — must never enter an image layer.
**/.env
deployments/.env
var/
deployments/var/
*.unseal

# Docs / planning / editor / design artifacts the build doesn't need.
.planning/
docs/
designs/
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.log
*.png
*.md
